==============================================================
  TICKET REQUIREMENTS  (extracted by Jira Agent)
==============================================================
  Ticket  : ADL-1700
  Summary : [APU Health Monitor] Create query for APU Health Monitor in Engine Folder

  Business Requirement:
    Create a query for APU Health Monitor that retrieves APU performance data from AMOS for APUs fitted to ASL AC Type B737NG aircraft. The query will join rotables and rotables_trend tables to extract APU part numbers, serial numbers, PSN identifiers, aircraft registration, reference dates, trend types (CT5), workorder information, and CT5ATP values, filtered for B737NG aircraft type and the latest reference date for each APU.

  Source Database : amos_acceptance
  Source Tables (3):
    - amos.rotables
    - amos.rotables_trend
    - amos.aircraft

  Output Fields (10):
    - partno: APU Part Number
    - serialno: APU Serial Number
    - psn: Unique PSN associated with each APU Serial Number
    - ac_registr: Aircraft Registration
    - rt_psn: PSN from rotables_trend table
    - ref_date: Reference Date (latest date only for each APU)
    - trend_type: Trend Type (CT5)
    - event_perfno_i: Workorder if present
    - value: CT5ATP value
    - ac_typ: Aircraft Type

  Transformations (4):
    - Join rotables table with rotables_trend table on PSN field
    - Join result with aircraft table on aircraft registration to obtain aircraft type
    - For each APU (identified by PSN), select only the row with the latest ref_date
    - Filter trend_type to only include CT5 records

  Filters (3):
    - aircraft.ac_typ = 'B737NG'
    - rotables_trend.trend_type = 'CT5'
    - rotables_trend.ref_date is the maximum date for each unique PSN

  Acceptance Criteria (7):
    - Query returns all APUs of type B737NG with their associated part numbers and serial numbers
    - Only the latest reference date is returned for each APU
    - CT5ATP values are correctly populated from rotables_trend.value
    - Workorder information is included when present in event_perfno_i
    - VDS is created in Engine Folder in Dremio
    - Query executes successfully against AMOS Acceptance database
    - All output fields match the Report entry column names as specified
