  Ticket  : ADL-1700
  Summary : [APU Health Monitor] Create query for APU Health Monitor in Engine Folder

  Business Requirement:
    Create a query for APU Health Monitor that extracts APU performance data from AMOS for APUs fitted to ASL AC Type B737NG aircraft. The query will join rotables and rotables_trend tables to provide APU part numbers, serial numbers, PSN identifiers, aircraft registration, reference dates, trend types (CT5), workorder information, and CT5ATP values, filtered to the latest reference date for each APU and B737NG aircraft type only.

  Source Database : amos_acceptance
  Source Tables (3):
    - amos.rotables
    - amos.rotables_trend
    - amos.aircraft

  Output Fields (9):
    - partno: APU Part Number
    - serialno: APU Serial Number
    - psn: Unique PSN associated with each APU Serial Number
    - ac_registr: Aircraft Registration
    - ref_date: Reference Date (latest date only for each APU)
    - trend_type: Trend Type (CT5)
    - event_perfno_i: Workorder if present
    - value: CT5ATP value
    - ac_typ: Aircraft Type

  Transformations (4):
    - Join rotables table with rotables_trend table on psn field
    - Join result with aircraft table on ac_registr field to filter by aircraft type
    - For each APU (identified by psn), select only the row with the maximum ref_date (latest reference date)
    - Retain event_perfno_i as-is, allowing NULL values where workorder is not present

  Filters (3):
    - aircraft.ac_typ = 'B737NG'
    - rotables_trend.trend_type = 'CT5'
    - rotables_trend.ref_date is the latest (maximum) date for each unique psn

  Acceptance Criteria (7):
    - Query returns all APUs of type B737NG with their latest CT5ATP trend data
    - Each APU appears only once, showing its most recent reference date
    - All required fields (partno, serialno, psn, ac_registr, ref_date, trend_type, event_perfno_i, value, ac_typ) are present in output
    - Workorder field (event_perfno_i) correctly shows NULL when no workorder is associated
    - VDS is created in Engine Folder
    - Query executes successfully against AMOS Acceptance database
    - Upon AMOS production go-live, data source can be switched to production without query logic changes
