  TICKET REQUIREMENTS  (extracted by Jira Agent)
==============================================================
  Ticket  : ADL-1699
  Summary : [APU Health Monitor] Create APU Health Monitor dashboard in Engine Status Dashboard

  Business Requirement:
    Create a new APU Health Monitor sheet in the existing Engine Dashboard that displays APU performance data with 8 key columns including part number, serial number, PSN, aircraft registration, reference date, CT5, workorder, and CT5ATP value. Apply conditional formatting to the CT5ATP value column based on threshold values to visually highlight performance status.

  Source Database : amos_postgres
  Source Tables (3):
    - amos.apu
    - amos.aircraft
    - amos.workorder

  Output Fields (8):
    - APU P/n: APU Part Number
    - APU S/n: APU Serial Number
    - PSN: Power Source Number or identifier
    - Aircraft Registration: Aircraft registration code or tail number
    - Reference Date: Date reference for the health monitoring record
    - CT5: Compressor Temperature 5 reading
    - Workorder: Associated workorder number
    - CT5ATP value: CT5 Actual To Plan value for APU performance monitoring

  Transformations (8):
    - Extract APU part number from APU master data
    - Extract APU serial number from APU master data
    - Extract PSN identifier from APU configuration
    - Join aircraft registration from aircraft master table
    - Convert reference date to standard date format
    - Extract CT5 temperature reading from APU performance metrics
    - Link workorder number from workorder table
    - Calculate or extract CT5ATP value as the actual to plan ratio

  Filters (2):
    - Include only active APU records
    - Include only records with valid CT5ATP values

  Acceptance Criteria (6):
    - All 8 columns are displayed in the APU Health Monitor sheet
    - CT5ATP value column displays with no formatting when value is less than 630
    - CT5ATP value column displays with amber background when value is equal to or greater than 630
    - CT5ATP value column displays with red background when value is equal to or greater than 660
    - Sheet is integrated into the existing Engine Dashboard
    - Data is accurately populated from source tables
